cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approach for the estimation of empowerment using deep neural networks trained on a sophisticated objective function. It also involves the use of a stochastic dynamic model in latent space, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with intrinsic motivation for artificial agents and the maximization of mutual information between agent actions and environment states. 

The paper involves visual observation only, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The use of the Water-Filling algorithm from information theory suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). These sub-categories often involve the use of optimization algorithms and control theory, which are related to the Water-Filling algorithm.
